A 45 minutes class of hardcore abdominal work. Focus on toning and defining
your abs and strengthening your back to improve posture and core strength.
Exercises are performed using bodyweight and a variety of equipment.

Hit the bags in a class with the intensity of a personal training session and
the motivation of a group environment. Each class begins with a warm up,
followed by a workout that engages strength, agility and endurance.

Move in aerobic movements performed to energetic music. Learn choreography
that incorporates hip-hop, soca, samba, salsa, merengue and mambo.

This class gives you a full body workout using hand weights. You’ll focus on
body parts from head to toe and finish with an ab workout.

An intense form of interval bike training. Tabata drills consist of 20 seconds of work
followed by 10 seconds of rest.

A calming, stress-relieving class to stretch and strengthen the body gradually. Emphasis is on building awareness of the breath and the body. Recommended for all levels looking for a soothing, relaxing, and restorative experience.
A high-energy interval training class that alternates between intermediate and advanced step choreographywith intensive muscle conditioning for a total body workout.

A fun, challenging class that fuses Pilates and Deep Stretch. You will burn
calories, tone muscles, improve balance and get a great stretch!

This is a weight lifting class designed to empower women to lift free weights in a group setting . The goals of WOW are to teach proper form, assist women in improving their posture, increasing their strength, and muscle pairing.

TRX leverages gravity and your bodyweight to perform hundreds of exercises.
You’re in control of how much you want to challenge yourself - because you
can simply adjust your body position to add or decrease resistance.

This class gives you a full body workout using hand weights. You’ll focus on
body parts from head to toe and finish with an ab workout.

Get your feet moving and heart pumping by combining strength and
endurance conditioning on a stationary bike. Jump, run and climb your way
through an intense session of aerobic and anaerobic training.

High Intensity Interval Training is a training technique in which you give all-out, one hundred percent effort through quick, intense bursts of exercise, followed by short, sometimes active, recovery periods.

An incredible fusion of core work and total body moves influenced by Pilates, but choreographed to your favorite Top 40 hits. This mat-based workout challenges students to rhytmhically flow from one exercise to the next, developing a stronger core.

This class is flexible to serve the needs of all students - it will get beginners into shape, it will challenge advanced athletes, & both men & women are welcome! Class format integrates combinations of punches, kicks, & heavy-bag work. Additional muscle and motion exercises are incorporated to strengthen and tone. You will have fun, reduce stress, & get an awesome workout.
